{
  "name": "kiro-recall: Promote Note",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Manually triggered hook invoked via /promote. Lists notes in 00-inbox/ for the user to select, reformats the selected note as an atomic Zettelkasten permanent note, writes it to 06-permanent/, and deletes the original from 00-inbox/.",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "You are running the kiro-recall promote hook. Your job is to take a raw capture note from the inbox, reformat it as an atomic Zettelkasten permanent note, write it to the permanent notes folder, and clean up the inbox.\n\n## Step 1 — Resolve vault path\n\nRead the file `powers/kiro-recall/mcp.json` from the workspace root. Locate the `mcpServers.mcp-obsidian.args` array. The vault path is the last element of that array.\n\nIf the file cannot be read or the path cannot be extracted, display this message and stop:\n\n> Couldn't resolve the vault path — check that `powers/kiro-recall/mcp.json` exists and contains a valid mcp-obsidian configuration.\n\nDo NOT surface stack traces, exception messages, or internal file paths. If the path is resolved, proceed to Step 2.\n\n## Step 2 — List inbox notes\n\nUse mcp-obsidian to list the contents of `00-inbox/` in the vault.\n\nFilter the results to markdown files only (files ending in `.md`).\n\nIf the count of markdown files is zero, display this message exactly and stop:\n\n> Your inbox is empty — nothing to promote yet.\n\nIf there are one or more markdown files, display a numbered list of the filenames:\n\n```\nInbox notes:\n  1. {filename}\n  2. {filename}\n  ...\n```\n\nThen ask the user:\n\n> Which note would you like to promote? (Enter a number or the filename.)\n\nWait for the user's response before proceeding to Step 3.\n\n## Step 3 — Read selected note\n\nIdentify the selected filename from the user's response (match by number from the list or by filename string).\n\nUse mcp-obsidian to read the full content of the selected file from `00-inbox/`.\n\nRecord the original filename — you will need it for deletion in Step 7.\n\nIf the read fails for any reason, display a human-readable error message and stop. Do NOT surface stack traces, exception messages, or internal file paths.\n\n## Step 4 — Reformat as Permanent Note\n\nAnalyze the content of the selected note and construct a Permanent Note with the following structure exactly:\n\n```\n# {Idea Title}\n\n## The idea\n{A single, self-contained statement of the core idea — one to two sentences maximum}\n\n## Why it matters\n{1–2 sentences on the significance or future relevance of this idea}\n\n## Connected to\n{[[wikilink]] references to related notes or concepts}\n\n## Source\n{Project name}, {session or context description}, {date in ISO 8601 format}\n```\n\nRules for each section:\n\n**# Title**: Derive a concise, descriptive title from the core idea in the source note. This becomes the idea's identity.\n\n**## The idea**: Distill the note down to one single, atomic idea. One to two sentences. No preamble, no context — just the idea itself.\n\n**## Why it matters**: 1–2 sentences on why this idea is worth keeping. Infer from the source note's \"Why it matters\" field if present, or reason from the content.\n\n**## Connected to**: Use `[[wikilink]]` format. Look for related concepts, projects, or notes mentioned in the source note. If no connections are apparent from the content, write `(none identified)` — do NOT fabricate wikilinks.\n\n**## Source**: Extract the project name and date from the source note's `## Project` and `## Date` fields if they exist. If not, infer the project from the filename (e.g. `2025-07-14-kiro-recall-session-hook.md` → project: `kiro-recall`, date: `2025-07-14`). Format as: `{project}, {brief session description}, {YYYY-MM-DD}`.\n\nHold this formatted Permanent Note in memory — you will need it for Steps 6 and (if write fails) the failure output.\n\n## Step 5 — Derive kebab-case filename\n\nDerive the permanent note filename from the idea title using this algorithm:\n\n1. Take the `# {Idea Title}` from Step 4 (without the `#` prefix).\n2. Lowercase all characters.\n3. Replace any character that is not `a-z`, `0-9`, or `-` with a hyphen.\n4. Collapse consecutive hyphens into a single hyphen.\n5. Strip any leading or trailing hyphens.\n6. Append `.md`.\n\nDo NOT add a date prefix. Permanent notes are evergreen — the filename should reflect the idea, not when it was created.\n\nExamples:\n- `\"Relevance Detection via Workspace Name\"` → `relevance-detection-via-workspace-name.md`\n- `\"Cold Vault: First-Session Handling\"` → `cold-vault-first-session-handling.md`\n\nRecord this filename — it is the permanent note's filename.\n\n## Step 6 — Write to 06-permanent/\n\nUse mcp-obsidian to write the Permanent Note content from Step 4 to `06-permanent/{filename}` in the vault, where `{filename}` is the filename derived in Step 5.\n\nIf the write succeeds, proceed to Step 7.\n\nIf the write fails for any reason:\n\n1. Display this message exactly:\n\n> Couldn't write to your vault — here's the reformatted note so you don't lose it:\n\n2. Immediately follow with the full Permanent Note content in a markdown code block.\n3. Stop. Do NOT attempt to delete the inbox note.\n4. Do NOT surface stack traces, exception messages, or internal file paths.\n\n## Step 7 — Delete from 00-inbox/\n\nThe write to `06-permanent/` succeeded. Now delete the original note from `00-inbox/`.\n\nUse mcp-obsidian to delete `00-inbox/{original-filename}` from the vault, where `{original-filename}` is the filename recorded in Step 3.\n\nIf the deletion succeeds, proceed to Step 8.\n\nIf the deletion fails for any reason, display this message and stop:\n\n> Promoted to `06-permanent/{filename}` — but couldn't remove the original from your inbox. You may want to delete `{original-filename}` manually.\n\nSubstitute the actual filenames. Do NOT surface stack traces, exception messages, or internal file paths.\n\n## Step 8 — Confirm\n\nBoth the write and the deletion succeeded. Display this message exactly, substituting the actual filename:\n\n> Promoted to `06-permanent/{filename}`.\n\nDisplay only this message. Do not include file system paths, stack traces, or any additional output."
  }
}
